	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "She was the wife of King Lālibalā who  played a major role during his reign. She was responsible\n                  for the fall of the metropolitan Mikāʿel II who had to return to Egypt after four years in Ethiopia.\n                  She is also credited with the building of some churches at Lālibalā. Her title can be interpreted as the \"Lady of biḥat\"\n               " .
